# Rule: 禁brain_obsidian_graph
# Token: 禁brain_obsidian_graph
# Priority: P0 (HIGHEST)
# Source: Drewgent P5-Ego + P0-brainstem — Obsidian Graph View Governance
# Created: 2026-05-14

禁brain_obsidian_graph 必vorq

FORBIDDEN: Create .md files in P-layer (P0~P6) or memories/ without proper wikilink connections
REASON: Obsidian graph view is Drewgent's self-visualization tool. Orphan nodes defeat the purpose.

## GRAPH INTEGRITY RULES

### New File Standard — P-layer .md Files
When creating any .md file inside P-layer or memories/ directories:

1. **Must declare parent node** — file must contain at least one wikilink to a parent/referenced node
2. **Must be referenced by parent** — the parent node must already contain or add a wikilink to this file
3. **Tag required** — frontmatter must include at least one #P-tag matching the layer

P-layer frontmatter tag convention:
  - P0-brainstem files:  #P0 #brainstem
  - P1-limbic files:      #P1 #limbic
  - P2-hippocampus files:  #P2 #hippocampus
  - P3-sensors files:     #P3 #sensors
  - P4-cortex files:      #P4 #cortex
  - P5-ego files:         #P5 #ego
  - P6-prefrontal files:  #P6 #prefrontal
  - memories/ files:      #wiki #memory

### Core Graph Nodes (must stay connected)
These files are the backbone of Drewgent's graph. Any new file in the P-layer should link to at least one of these:

  [[P5-ego/SELF_MODEL]]           ← P5-Ego (identity anchor)
  [[P1-limbic/persona/SOUL]]      ← P1-Limbic (voice anchor)
  [[P3-sensors/gateway/drewgent-architecture-dataflow]]  ← P3-Sensors (data flow)
  [[P4-cortex/knowledge/NEURONFS_RULES]]  ← P4-Cortex (governance)
  [[P0-brainstem/brain/Drewgent-brain/P0-brainstem/禁karpathy_coding_principles]] ← P0 (coding rules)

### .neuron Files (Brain Rules)
Brain rules (`.neuron` files) in P0-brainstem/禁/ and P0-brainstem/ are first-class graph nodes.
Each `.neuron` file must connect to at least one Core Graph Node via wikilinks in its `links:` frontmatter.
The rule enforces that newly created `.neuron` files follow the same bidirectional linking standard.

Integration workflow for new .neuron files:
  1. Create .neuron file with frontmatter: title, type, space, rule_token, rule_priority, rule_source, created, links
  2. links: must include at least one Core Graph Node
  3. Add wikilink from the referenced Core Graph Node → new .neuron file
  4. For P-layer .neuron files in P0-brainstem/禁/: also add bidirectional link to 禁brain_obsidian_graph
  5. Verify: both directions exist in frontmatter links:
       - new.neuron links → core node
       - core node links → new.neuron

### Wikilink Format
  - Intra-folder:      [[filename]]
  - Cross-folder:       [[folder/subfolder/filename]]
  - To section:         [[filename#Section Name]]
  - Brain rules (.neuron): [[P0-brainstem/brain/Drewgent-brain/P0-brainstem/禁/禁rulename]]

### Schema Enforcement
New files in memories/ must follow SCHEMA.md conventions:
  - entities/   → [[entities/]] category files
  - concepts/   → [[concepts/index]]
  - insights/   → [[insights/index]] + daily log
  - Frontmatter: title, tags, created, updated

### Graph Review
Before declaring any task complete, verify:
  - New .md file has wikilink(s) to at least one existing node
  - At least one existing node links back to the new file
  - Frontmatter tags include correct #P-tag
  - No broken wikilinks (file referenced actually exists)

## VORQ PATTERN
When user asks to create any .md file in P-layer or memories/:
  1. Ask: which existing node does this connect to?
  2. Add wikilink from existing node → new file
  3. Add wikilink from new file → existing node(s)
  4. Verify: both directions confirmed

## EXCEPTION
Auto-generated files (cron output, session transcripts, vector index) — excluded from graph integrity rules. These are logged in vectors.db but do not need wikilinks.

